      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/2168432/" class="title-link">月之暗面</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-2168432"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/1678774/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1678774-41.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/1678774/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">绿洲</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2009-07-26"
      class="main-meta">2009-07-26 16:01:09</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_2168432_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  我承认会有少数故事，前百分之九十看得我觉得不过如此，但到最后的结局处，却震得我浑身一颤。  比如《背德者》和《基督最后的诱惑》。  结果我居然在明朝那些事儿的结尾体会到了同样的感觉。由此可见当年明月是个聪明的作家，他知道一个故事想要被人记住，最方便莫过于在结局...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/2168432/#comments">(3回应)</a>
